removeChild

public void removeChild(org.mt4j.components.MTComponent in)
Remove the child component from the scene. Used internally. May be used externally to remove some components. Warning: be careful not to remove node components. That is handled by the Tree system (remove/hide its corresponding Node and call Tree.update()).

Parameters:
in - the component to remove from the scene

makeDefaultLine

public org.mt4j.components.visibleComponents.shapes.MTLine makeDefaultLine()
Construct a default line. This generates a simple MTLine of 0px (aka 1px regardless of transformation). This method is typically used to populate Edge objects with components. Note that the returned Line is customized to prevent frustum culling when its start and end points are not in view.

Returns:
a simple MTLine
